		{
			"id": 1,
			"parent": 9,
			"text": "In many chronic inflammatory disorders , glucocorticoid ( GC ) insensitivity is a challenging clinical problem",
			"relation": "BACKGROUND"
		},
		{
			"id": 2,
			"parent": 1,
			"text": "associated with life-threatening disease progression . <S>",
			"relation": "CAUSE-RESULT"
		},
		{
			"id": 3,
			"parent": 1,
			"text": "The molecular basis of GC insensitivity , however , is unknown . <S>",
			"relation": "COMPARISON"
		},
		{
			"id": 4,
			"parent": 1,
			"text": "Alternative splicing of the GC receptor ( R ) pre-messenger RNA generates a second GCR ,",
			"relation": "ELABORATION"
		},
		{
			"id": 5,
			"parent": 4,
			"text": "termed GCR-beta ,",
			"relation": "ELABORATION"
		},
		{
			"id": 6,
			"parent": 4,
			"text": "which does not bind GCs",
			"relation": "ELABORATION"
		},
		{
			"id": 7,
			"parent": 6,
			"text": "but antagonizes the transactivating activity of the classic GCR ,",
			"relation": "COMPARISON"
		},
		{
			"id": 8,
			"parent": 7,
			"text": "termed GCR-alpha . <S>",
			"relation": "ELABORATION"
		},
		{
			"id": 9,
			"parent": 0,
			"text": "In the current study , we demonstrate that GC-insensitive asthma is associated with a significantly higher number of GCR-beta-immunoreactive cells in peripheral blood than GC-sensitive asthmatics or normal controls . <S>",
			"relation": "ROOT"
		},
		{
			"id": 10,
			"parent": 9,
			"text": "Furthermore , we show that patients with GC-insensitive asthma have cytokine-induced abnormalities in the DNA binding capability of the GCR . <S>",
			"relation": "ADDITION"
		},
		{
			"id": 11,
			"parent": 10,
			"text": "These abnormalities can be reproduced by transfection of cell lines with the GCR-beta gene",
			"relation": "ELABORATION"
		},
		{
			"id": 12,
			"parent": 11,
			"text": "resulting in significant reduction of their GCR-alpha DNA binding capacity . <S>",
			"relation": "CAUSE-RESULT"
		},
		{
			"id": 13,
			"parent": 9,
			"text": "We conclude that increased expression of GCR-beta is cytokine inducible",
			"relation": "FINDINGS"
		},
		{
			"id": 14,
			"parent": 13,
			"text": "and may account for GC insensitivity in this common inflammatory condition . <S>",
			"relation": "ADDITION"
		}
	]
}